<br>
1)  Never, ever, ever, give anybody anything without getting your item in return.  No matter what the excuse, no matter how much you trust them, no matter if it's a guildmate, no matter if it's the freakin' Pope.  Don't do it.  There is absolutely *NO* valid reason to risk your items and plat this way.  If they are too damn lazy to put everything on one twink/seller, that that's no reason for you to make up for it.<br>
<br>
2)  Because no one ever listens to common sense, or becasue you'll run across some deal that's just 'too good to be true' and you just can't help yourself and you *have* to break rune #1, here's the antiote:<br>
<br>
2a)  Fact:  GM's and Guide freakin' hate dealing with Trade Scammers.  it's always one person's word again anothers, and only GM's can verify a trade did or didn't take place. <br>
<br>
2b)  Guide's and GM *REALLY, REALLY* hate people that try to pull trade scams, and if given the proper information, will come down on them like holy vengenance.<br>
<br>
How do you give them the information they need?  /report.<br>
<br>
Love /report.  /report is your salvation.  /report is your god.  /report is unquestioned proof of a conversation, and nothing will work faster to get a GM or Guide on your side.<br>
<br>
Now, if you're gonna risk doing a double trade, you need to get the other party to specifically, and explicitly state the terms of the arrangement.  you must *Demand* that they state it to you in terms like this:<br>
<br>
&quot;If you give me 25k, I will relog as soansdo and give you the Fungi Yunic&quot;<br>
<br>
The instant you see that, type /report soandso while it's still on your screen.  That dumps that statement to a log, and is proof of what they told you would occur.  <br>
<br>
Basically, /report everything you can.  If you're screwed already, scroll back and /report everything you possibly can.  It's imperative that you get in those /reports immediately, as it's the only proof you've got.  If you need to zone so it doesn't scroll off so fast, do it.  /report takes the current chat screen that you are viewing, and saves it to a log only GM's can access - there's no penality for over-using it, so arm yourself with it constantly.<br>
<br>
Now, with all that said, if you still fucked up, gave your stuff away, and then didn't get a report, you have one, last shot.<br>
<br>
If you can enage the scammer in conversation after the fact, and they specifically state to you something along the lines of 'yeah, I ripped you off, bite me', or basically any statement stating guilt, /report it immediately, and /petition.  <br>
<br>
If you can do these things, there is nothing the scammer can do to deny the evidence.  Even if they log off and don't log back on, they can be tracked IF you did a /report that proved the deception.  GM's can find alts, they can figure out who the item was transferred to, they can find multiple account holders - they just have to have justification to do so.<br>
